HEADWORD: Hamster
<hw>Ham"ster</hw> <pr>(-st⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>hamster</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small European
rodent (<spn>Cricetus frumentarius</spn>). It is remarkable for having a
pouch on each side of the jaw, under the skin, and for its migrations.
Hamsters are commonly kept as a pets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

